-- Deutsche Bank to Sell U.S. Shares on Sao Paulo Exchange, Estado Reports
-- Laura Price
-- 2010-04-23T11:15:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-23/deutsche-bank-to-sell-u-s-shares-on-sao-paulo-exchange-estado-reports.html

          
          
             Deutsche Bank AG made an agreement 
with BM&FBovespa SA to sell U.S. stocks on the Sao Paulo 
exchange, O Estado de S. Paulo reported, citing Ricardo 
Nascimento, custody director at the bankâ€™s local unit.  
 Deutsche Bank will buy shares of U.S. companies and issue 
them as Brazilian depositary receipts, the newspaper said. 
Individual investors will be able to purchase them through 
funds, Estado said. The bank will start by selling shares in 10
U.S. companies, the paper cited Nascimento as saying.  
